%% Diagram: Cache stampede on TTL expiry vs. mitigated path with request coalescing
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Clients as N concurrent clients
    participant CDN
    participant Origin

    Note over CDN: Hot key TTL just expired
    Clients->>CDN: GET /popular (xN)
    CDN->>Origin: GET /popular (xN, no coalescing)
    Note over Origin: Spike: load proportional to N
    Origin-->>CDN: 200 OK (xN)
    CDN-->>Clients: 200 OK

    Note over CDN: Same scenario with request coalescing
    Clients->>CDN: GET /popular (xN)
    CDN->>Origin: GET /popular (x1)
    Note over CDN: N-1 requests held until single fetch returns
    Origin-->>CDN: 200 OK (x1)
    CDN-->>Clients: 200 OK (xN)
